x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">After leaving Savan=
nah, my film crew and I drove up to Clemson University, just in time for so=
me crisp fall weather in the foothills. Yeah, I know South Carolina isn=E2=
=80=99t a battleground state like Georgia. But Clemson is a Republican-lean=
ing campus, and given the attention being lavished on the =E2=80=9CBro Vote=
=E2=80=9D by reporters in recent months, I wanted to get inside the minds o=
f young men who are planning to vote for Trump. <br/><br/>My biggest takeaw=
ay on campus is that support for Trump isn=E2=80=99t just about Zyn or <b>J=
oe</b> <b>Rogan</b> or the UFC celebrities who have gone MAGA. Some culture=
 war topics came up. One dude named <b>Reaves</b>, who was wearing Croakies=
 and said he loves to hunt and fish, told me he supports Trump because of =
=E2=80=9Cguns.=E2=80=9D Another student, <b>James</b> <b>Regan</b>, argued =
that =E2=80=9Cyoung men are going to the right just because
of how active and woke the far left has gotten. I think it kind of annoys t=
hem a little bit.=E2=80=9D But Regan, and most of the Clemson students I sp=
oke to, weren=E2=80=99t buffoonish caricatures plucked out of the manospher=
e, parroting the Nelk Boys or complaining about pronoun culture. They had g=
ood reasons to support Trump, and they understood, too, why young women wer=
e backing Harris.<br/><br/>I talked to mostly white men on campus. Several =
talked about how they thought Trump was =E2=80=9Cstrong=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=
=9Ca fighter,=E2=80=9D with a few referencing that now-famous photo of a bl=
oody and defiant Trump raising his fist after a shooter nearly took his lif=
e in Butler, Pennsylvania, over the summer. But none of these men talked ab=
out Harris with the sexism or contempt I heard from young Trump supporters =
about <b>Hillary</b> <b>Clinton</b> back in 2016. =E2=80=9CShe=E2=80=99s a =
really good speaker and I understand her appeal,=E2=80=9D said a student na=
med <b>Anthony Colella</b>. =E2=80=9CShe is really optimistic. We saw it
in the debate. She knows how to rally people behind her. But my issue is, w=
e don=E2=80=99t know exactly what she wants. What is her plan? I=E2=80=99m =
not sure. I kind of think it=E2=80=99s like, =E2=80=98High on vibes, low on=
 substance.=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Like Anthony, several other young me=
n went out of their way to offer qualified praise of Harris=E2=80=99s perso=
nal attributes and political talents, in particular her debate performance =
against Trump. It was a small counterpoint to the claim Obama made in Pitts=
burgh, that young male voters are outright contemptuous of a woman in polit=
ics. =E2=80=9CIn that debate, she shocked me a little bit,=E2=80=9D said <b=
>Geoffrey</b> <b>Hunt</b>, a freshman pounding a Celsius on his way to a ma=
rketing class. =E2=80=9CI really do try to have an unbiased opinion, and sh=
e did a lot better than I thought that she was going to do. I was watching =
and looking at how she carries herself. She has this homey, good, welcoming=
 feeling about her. I just don=E2=80=99t think any of her policies or anyth=
ing
she=E2=80=99s done necessarily supports that.=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>These youn=
g men also said they understood the growing gender gap inside Gen Z, and se=
veral said they sympathized with young women moving to Harris because of he=
r loud and proud support for abortion rights. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s pretty =
clear that what=E2=80=99s pulling women left is her stance on abortion, and=
 I totally get that,=E2=80=9D Regan told me. =E2=80=9CAs a man, abortion do=
esn=E2=80=99t have as much to do with me as it does women.=E2=80=9D<br/><br=
/>But most of the Clemson students cited one of two main reasons for suppor=
ting Trump: They were either socially conservative pro-lifers, or they figu=
red Trump would do a better job bringing down the cost of living and managi=
ng the economy. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m not alone in thinking that this electi=
on is a pick of necessary evils,=E2=80=9D said <b>Will</b> <b>Lawson</b>, a=
 junior from Apex, North Carolina. =E2=80=9CI mean, you don=E2=80=99t love =
all of Trump&#39;s rhetoric, but I also understand that he=E2=80=99s needed=
 for this country. I don=E2=80=99t
understand how you can look at the past four years and understand that Kama=
la Harris has been the vice president, she=E2=80=99s part of this administr=
ation, and the very simple point that=E2=80=99s just compelling to me is li=
ke, <i>Do I want four more years of this?</i> And for me, that=E2=80=99s no=
=2E Grocery prices were down. Gas price=
s going down. Immigrants are coming ov=
er the border. It just feels like the Democratic Party isn=E2=80=99t lookin=
g out for me as a citizen.=E2=80=9D<br/></td>
